Package: yadorilink
Version: @VERSION@
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: yadorilink project <juntaki@users.noreply.github.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/juntaki/yadorilink
Depends: libc6
Description: Peer-to-peer file sync -- CLI and daemon
 yadorilink is a peer-to-peer file synchronization tool. This package
 installs the yadorilink CLI (`yadorilink`) and the yadorilink-daemon sync
 daemon, plus a systemd --user service unit for the daemon
 (/usr/lib/systemd/user/yadorilink-daemon.service).
 .
 This is a CLI/daemon-only build: it does not include the desktop tray
 application (yadorilink-desktop-app), which is not built for Linux in
 this release. See https://github.com/juntaki/yadorilink for docs.
 .
 The systemd user unit is installed but NOT enabled automatically; run
 `systemctl --user enable --now yadorilink-daemon` after installing to
 start the daemon at login with crash-restart supervision.
